<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p><a href="http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa224033">http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa224033</a>(SQL.80).aspx</p>

<p>Microsoft SQL Server does support ANSI standard delimited identifiers.  Use double-quotes for identifier delimiters.</p>

<p>This is the behavior to use when the mode QUOTED_IDENTIFIER is ON.  This mode is on by default in the OLEDB, ODBC, and DBLIB interfaces.</p>

